headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell had 27 points and 11 assists as the red-hot Utah Jazz improved their NBA-best record with a 103-95 road win over the Indiana Pacers on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell leads surging Jazz past Pacers

events.name: Miami Heat at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo had 24 points and 11 rebounds, Jimmy Butler had a big second half and just missed a triple-double and the Miami Heat beat the New York Knicks 109-103 on Sunday in the opener of a home-and-home series.
headlines.shortLinkText: Adebayo, Butler help Heat beat Knicks in opener of series

headlines.description: — Terry Rozier had 26 points with five 3-pointers, Gordon Hayward added 25 points and the Charlotte Hornets beat the Washington Wizards 119-97 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rozier scores 26, Hayward 25 as Hornets rout Wizards 119-97

headlines.description: — Mikal Bridges scored 19 points, Devin Booker had 18 points and 11 assists and the Phoenix Suns held on to beat the Boston Celtics 100-91 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns hang on for 100-91 victory over the Celtics

headlines.description: — De’Aaron Fox scored 36 points, Buddy Hield added 22 and the Sacramento Kings beat the Los Angeles Clippers 113-110 on Sunday for their fourth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Streaking Kings win 4th straight, beat Clippers 113-110
